               <head>Maimonides' Mishneh Torah</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287 lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
                  <summary>SeferʾAhavah - Sefer Ḳedushah from Maimonides' Mishneh Torah.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jpr-Hebr" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="1" />
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_100185495 http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">Maimonides, Moses,
                  1135-1204</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf_100185495 http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">משה בן
                  מימון</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="he">משנה תורה (ספר אהבה-קדושה)</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Mishneh Torah (Sefer ʾAhavah- Sefer Ḳedushah)</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <note>
                        <p>Contains: Sefer ʾAhavah (Hilkhot Tefilin, mezuzah ṿe-Sefer Torah 1:14) - Sefer
                  Ḳedushah (Hilkhot Iśure Biʾah 18:14).</p>
                        <p>Hilkhot Maʾakhalot aśurot 2:13-4:17 are bound at the head of the manuscript.</p>
                        <p>Several translations into Persian are in the margins and between the lines.</p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon xml:lang="he">"נשלמה זה ארבעה ספרים ברחמי שמיא ליום שני בשבה דהוא ארבע יומין
                לירח טבת על יד הצעיר העני והנאמן שר שלום בן ה'ה'ה'ה'ה' רבי ומראי ר' שמואל נ"ע
                דמתקליב מ’ עמראני זלה"ה דשנת אלפא ותמני מאה ושיתין וחד שנין לשטרות"<locus n="243v" />
                     </colophon>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="1r" to="40r" />
                        <title>Sefer ʾAhavah</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Ff. 1r-19v: Hilkhot Tefilin, mezuzah ṿe-Sefer Torah; ff. 19v-23r: Hilkhot
                    Tsitsit; ff. 23r-37r: Hilkhot Berakhot; ff. 37r-40r: Hilkhot Milah.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="41v" to="165r" />
                        <title>Sefer Zemanim</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Ff. 42r-89v: Hilkhot Shabat; ff. 89v-101r: Hilkhot ʿEruvin; ff. 101r-103r:
                    Hilkhot Shevitat ʿaśor; ff. 103r-115r: Hilkhot Shevitat yom ṭov; ff. 115r-124v:
                    Hilkhot Ḥamets u-matsah; ff. 124v-132r: Hilkhot Shofar ṿe-sukah ṿe-lulav; ff.
                    132r-135r: Hilkhot Sheḳalim; ff. 135v-155v: Hilkhot Ḳidush ha-ḥodesh; ff.
                    155v-164v: Hilkhot Taʿaniyot.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="165v" to="243v" />
                        <title>Sefer Nashim</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Ff. 165v-202r: Hilkhot Ishut; ff. 202r-224r: Hilkhot Gerushin; ff. 224r-236v:
                    Hilkhot Yibum ṿe-ḥalitsah; ff. 236v-239r: Hilkhot Naʿarah betulah; ff.
                    239r-243v: Hilkhot Śoṭah.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="244v" to="270v" />
                        <title>Sefer Ḳedushah</title>
                        <note>
                           <p>Ff. 245r-270v: Hilkhot ʾisure biʾah 1:1-18:14.</p>
                           <p>Incomplete.</p>
                        </note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Yellowish oriental paper.</support>
                        <extent>270 folios (iii+270+ii)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>290</height>
                              <width>192</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>205</height>
                              <width>140</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliation in Arabic numerals in pencil.</p>
                           <p>F. 244r is blank.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>Indeterminable due to too tight binding.</p>
                           <p>Catchword on every verso.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>Ff. 1-9 and 270: damaged but have been restored (silk gauze).</p>
                           <p>Usage stains, slight liquid damage.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
                           <p>Chapter heading are in slightly larger charaters.</p>
                           <p>Ruling is visible.</p>
                           <p>On some of the pages, the words in the last line written diagonally.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     <summary>Persian Hebrew square script of the 16th century. The scribe was Śar-Shalom
                ben Shemuel ʿImrani.</summary>
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole" />
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote>
                        <p />
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Scribbles, pen trials in Hebrew script on ff. 40r-41r.</p>
                     <p>OF. 165r: shetar (legal document) in Persian which mentions among others: Avraham
                ben Binyamin, and Gamal ben Avraham Kohen Karazoni; witnesses: <quote xml:lang="he">מ' דוד בן מ' עמראן, יוסף בן אברהם בנימין, יהודה בן יעקב אלישע, אלישע
                שמחה</quote>.
                     </p>
                     <p>French note on front flyleaf (iii)v: 'No. 29 - Un tome du livre de Harem Bem
                transcrit [...]'</p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding>
                        <p>BM in-house.</p>
                        <p>Spine: 'Moses Ben Maimūn. Mishneh Torah. III-V. Hebrew &amp; Persian. Brit. Mus.
                  Oriental 10,043.'</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
